---
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta name="description" content="Privacy Policy for Ghost — Personal Location Journal" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=IBM+Plex+Mono:ital,wght@0,100;0,200;0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,100;1,200;1,300;1,400;1,500;1,600;1,700&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <title>Ghost — Privacy Policy</title>
  </head>
  <body class="bg-white text-gray-800 min-h-screen">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16 lg:px-8">

      <header class="mb-12">
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">iOS App</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Ghost</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-500">Privacy Policy</p>
      </header>

      <div class="space-y-10 text-sm leading-relaxed text-gray-700">

        <section>
          <p>
            Ghost is a personal location journal. It runs quietly in the background, detects when
            you arrive at and leave places, and builds a private daily timeline — entirely on your
            device. Your data belongs to you and only you.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Information Collected</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">
            Ghost uses Apple's <span class="font-medium">CLVisit API</span> to detect significant arrivals
            and departures. This requires "Always On" background location permission. The app records:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 pl-2">
            <li>Visit timestamps (arrival and departure times)</li>
            <li>Approximate location coordinates of visited places</li>
            <li>Place names and labels you assign manually</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            The app does <span class="font-medium">not</span> perform continuous GPS tracking. Location
            is only sampled at the moment a visit event is triggered by the operating system.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">How It's Used</h2>
          <p>
            Location data is used solely to build your personal timeline within the app. It is never
            used for advertising, profiling, analytics, or any purpose beyond displaying your own
            history back to you.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Data Storage</h2>
          <p>
            All data — visit records, saved places, routes, and your full location history — is stored
            exclusively in the app's local SwiftData database on your iPhone. There is no account,
            no login, and no backend server. The developer has no ability to access, view, or retrieve
            any of your data.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            You can delete all stored data at any time from within the app via
            <span class="font-medium">Settings → Clear All Data</span>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Third Parties</h2>
          <p>
            Ghost contains no analytics SDKs, no advertising frameworks, no crash reporting services,
            and no third-party trackers of any kind. Nothing is uploaded to or shared with any external
            service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Ghost does not collect any personal data from anyone, including children under the age of
            13. Because all data remains on-device and is never transmitted, the app does not implicate
            COPPA or similar children's privacy regulations. Ghost is not directed at children.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Contact</h2>
          <p>
            If you have questions about this privacy policy or the app, you can reach the developer by
            email. Feedback sent from within the app composes an email on your device — nothing is
            transmitted automatically. Any log lines attached to a feedback email are included only
            with your explicit knowledge and action.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            <a
              href="mailto:carl@holmquist.studio"
              class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
            >
              carl@holmquist.studio
            </a>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="pt-4 border-t border-gray-100">
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Last updated: April 16, 2026</p>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
